That's a really good question about the project timeline. Honestly, I think if we break it down into two-week sprints rather than month-long blocks, we can get feedback faster and adjust before we're too far down the wrong path. I've seen teams get stuck waiting for perfection before sharing, and it usually just wastes time. Let's set up a quick sync to map out the first sprint? I'm free Tuesday afternoon. Also, the new software update seems to work fine on my machine, no major bugs spotted yet. I wanted to follow up on your request about the database access. The admin team confirmed that read-only permissions can be granted by end of week. Just submit a ticket with the specific tables you need to query. Should be straightforward. Let me know if you need write access, that requires a separate approval. Otherwise, everything is on track for the next release.

